room_title: Escape room "The Missing Five" by Locked Up Philly in Philadelphia
review: Well constructed room. Countdown clock in room. Doesn't have the typical combination lock puzzles; instead uses some clever and novel ways to "unlock" the next puzzle., even more so than 1409. It's one of the more physical rooms we've done.  It's not scary. It's a little creepy if you've seen the "Saw" movies, but not that bad if you aren't familiar with those movies.  Suitable for a group of 3-4. Overall a very fun room.
